Initial commit: gethrelay - Ethereum P2P Relay Node with JSON-RPC Proxy

This is a focused fork of go-ethereum optimized for relay node functionality.

Features:
- Lightweight P2P relay node without blockchain state storage
- JSON-RPC proxy with local eth_sendRawTransaction handling
- Upstream request proxying for all other RPC methods
- Docker support with optimized multi-stage builds
- GitHub Actions CI/CD with Hive integration tests
- Comprehensive test coverage (unit + integration)

Changes from upstream:
- Removed unused command binaries (geth, clef, evm, etc.)
- Added gethrelay implementation (P2P relay + RPC proxy)
- Added Docker Compose configurations
- Added GitHub Actions workflow
- Updated documentation for gethrelay
- Codebase cleanup and optimization

Package size: ~351K LOC
gethrelay: ~1.1K LOC (863 source + 240 tests)

